com.unvired.sync.in
Class SyncDataHandler

java.lang.Object
  com.unvired.sync.in.SyncDataHandler

public class SyncDataHandler
extends java.lang.Object

SyncDataHandler handles synchronous application data. SyncDataHandler connects to the server, gets the response and parses the incoming synchronous responses. Data is automatically saved or returned to the application for handling. Only data in IBXML format can be saved by the SyncDataHandler. In all above cases before inserting or updating data the header data structure is checked for conflict. If there is a conflict between the incoming data and the data stored on the device (due to local changes in the application on the device) then the conflict handler registered by the application is called. No action is taken by the framework for conflict.
